[src:solid-state-physics/free-electron-model] This formula takes into account the spin degeneracy but does not consider a possible energy shift due to the bottom of the conduction band.
[src:solid-state-physics/free-electron-model] For 2D the density of states is constant and for 1D is inversely proportional to the square root of the electron energy.
[src:solid-state-physics/free-electron-model] The chemical potential $\mu$ of electrons in a solid is also known as the Fermi level and, like the related Fermi energy, often denoted $E_{\rm {F}}$ .
