[src:solid-state-physics/free-electron-model] The perturbative approach is justified as the Fermi temperature is usually of about 105 K for a metal, hence at room temperature or lower the Fermi energy $E_{\rm {F}}(T=0)$ and the chemical potential $E_{\rm {F}}(T>0)$ are practically equivalent.
